  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "TAM is commonly employed in information and communication technology studies to elucidate user acceptance behaviour, with a specific focus on predicting the adoption and acceptance of new technologies.",
    "According to Davis (1989), users generally understand that technology enhances performance in their respective areas of work.",
    "Liu (2004) outlines that TAM is founded on two key premises: perceived usefulness and perceived ease of use.",
    "This implies that individuals' acceptance and use of technology hinge on their perceptions of its utility in their lives and how it facilitates their work or their daily activities.",
    "In the context of this study, the application of the technology acceptance model seeks to comprehend the acceptance and integration of ChatGPT in the postgraduate studies of students engaged in South Africa's historically disadvantaged universities."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "According to Davis (1989), users generally understand that technology enhances performance in their respective areas of work.",
